                If the site suddenly starts failing or refusing to load, try clicking the button below or follow the steps in the <small>`Why is the site suddenly not working?`</small> section.
            </p>
            <a href="/service-worker.js" class="btn btn-danger" role="button">Force Update</a>
        </div>
        <div class="alert mt-4" role="alert">
            <div class="media" style="padding-top: 12px; padding-bottom: 12px; border: 1px solid transparent;">
                <Question Title="Who is this site maintained by?" ShortAnswer="Pseudonym Ltd">
                    <Answer>
                        <p>
                            This site is run by Pseudonym Ltd, which is a one man company run by <Link DisplayText="Tom Day" Url="https://www.linkedin.com/in/tom-day-684a0ba6" CaptionText="LinkedIn" />.
                            Tom participated in the <b>Crypto20</b> <small>ICO</small> making his debut investment in the crypto space.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            In 2020, Tom took part in Invictus Capital's community developer program,
                            aiming to incentivize developers and tech savvy people alike in the space to make tools for the wider Invictus community.
                            This product is the result of that program.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <b>Note:</b> Although incentivized by Invictus Capital, this tool is maintained 100% separately from Invictus Capital - please don't bother them with stuff to do with this site!
                        </p>
                    </Answer>
                </Question>
                <Question Title="Why is the site suddenly not working?" ShortAnswer="The site has probably updated. You should clear your cache.">
                    <Answer>
                        <p>
                            This site is made using Blazor. For all of its technical greatness, its still pretty bad when it comes to updating our website.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            If you find the site suddenly stops working, it could be us! But before sending us a bug report, try the following:
                        </p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Press F12 if you're on a desktop, or if on a tablet device or mobile, navigate to the developer tools section of your browser.</li>
                            <li>
                                If on desktop, a new pane will appear - click the "Application" tab and hit clear cache. This will clear the cache for this site.
                                <br />
                                <br />
                                <p>
                                    <b>Note 1:</b> Watch out for cookies - you probably want to uncheck any tick boxes that refer to clearing cookies, you'll want to keep them.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <b>Note 2:</b> If you have the option, tick the checkbox "update on reload" under service workers, this should solve the issue for you permanently.
                                </p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                If you're using a mobile or tablet device, your browser may not have a "developer" mode. In this case, you'll have to clear your global cache.
                                <p>
                                    To clear your global cache, you'll need to go into your settings, under the privacy section on your browser, there should be a clear method to clearing out your cache.
                                </p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                If you're using the app on your tablet or phone, just uninstall the app and reinstall it from the website, to be safe.
                                <br />
                                <br />
                                <p>
                                    <b>Note:</b> We're working on a way to sort this one out, as it's not ideal!
                                </p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </Answer>
                </Question>
            </div>
            <div class="media" style="padding-top: 12px; padding-bottom: 12px; border: 1px solid transparent;">
                <Question Title="Where does the data on this site come from?" ShortAnswer="A number of reputable crypto sources, which are then cached.">
                    <Answer>
                        <p>
                            Data on this site is collected from a variety of sources to maintain data integrity. Most of this data is collected and then cached in our own storage systems.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <span>Below is a list of current data sources:</span>
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    <b><Link DisplayText="Invictus Capital" Url="https://invictuscapital.com" CaptionText="Extenal Link" /></b>
                        <p>
                            Would be difficult to create a Invictus Capital Portfolio tracker without having NAV data from these guys.
                        </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <b><Link DisplayText="Bloxy" Url="https://bloxy.info" CaptionText="Extenal Link" /></b>
                            <p>
                                Bloxy is used to collect transaction data for all of the invictus funds, which we then cache on our own data clusters for quicker access.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <b><Link DisplayText="Ethplorer" Url="https://ethplorer.io" CaptionText="Extenal Link" /></b>
                            <p>
                                Ethplorer is used to collect transactional operation data to obtain a finer granularity of detail. These also get cached for quicker access.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <b><Link DisplayText="Infura" Url="https://infura.io" CaptionText="Extenal Link" /></b>
                            <p>
                                Infura provides a <small>RPC</small> which is used to collate data about token holdings across addresses.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <b><Link DisplayText="Lightstreams" Url="https://explorer.lightstreams.io" CaptionText="Extenal Link" /></b>
                            <p>
                                Lightstreams provides a <small>RPC</small> to connect to their Lightstream network. This is a holding of the <b>Invictus Hyperion Fund</b> and is used to collate data about <small>PHT</small> holdings across addresses.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        </ul>
                        </p>
                    </Answer>
                </Question>
                <Question Title="How often is data refreshed on this site?" ShortAnswer="Hourly.">
                    <Answer>
                        <p>
                            There are a number of features on this site which update at different intervals, but its safe to say that the site data in general updates hourly.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Here is a quick breakdown of features and their update intervals:
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    <b>Transactions</b> - Hourly
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <b>Fiat Exchange Rates</b> - Hourly
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <b>Staking Power</b> - Hourly
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <b>Invictus Fund Prices</b> - Live
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <b>Non Invictus Fund Prices</b> - Live
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </p>
                    </Answer>
                </Question>
            </div>
            <div class="media" style="padding-top: 12px; padding-bottom: 12px; border: 1px solid transparent;">
                <Question Title="How do I report a problem?" ShortAnswer="Send an email to Tom - tom.day@psuedonym.org.uk">
                    <Answer>
                        <p>
                            If you find an issue on the site, please email Tom <a href="mailto:tom.day@psuedonym.org.uk">here</a>.
                            Before you do, try clearing your browser cache, worth a shot, and usually works!
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <b>Note:</b> To best service your issue, please be as descriptive as possible in your email, and be sure to use a couple of screen shots.
                            Try to include a rough time estimate of when you encountered the issue too!
                        </p>
                    </Answer>
                </Question>
                <Question Title="Is this site still being developed?" ShortAnswer="Yes - watch this space!">
                    <Answer>
                        <p>
                            The site is constantly being improved and updated. There is a maximum monthly budget for running costs, which will hopefully grow over time.
